data.text:
The Shaw Birthplace is the place of birth of the playwright George Bernard Shaw, now a restored Victorian home giving insight into the domestic life of the 19th Century middle classes. The Centre is run by volunteers.

The House is currently closed to visitors (despite what it says on many websites).
